    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Vatican Museums",
          "url": "https://goo.gl/maps/2RKyE6Q95uUpEqZF9"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The Vatican is home to an extensive museum complex, where popes have collected valuable works of art for centuries. Today, it houses one of the largest art collections in the world. It’s said that there are so many exhibits that if you spent one minute viewing each of them, the entire tour would last 12 years. The Vatican Palace contains 8 museums, 5 galleries, the Apostolic Library, the Borgia Apartments, the Raphael Rooms, and the famous Sistine Chapel. This private papal chapel is also where the papal conclaves take place when a new pope is elected."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The Sistine Chapel is renowned for its stunning frescoes by Michelangelo. The Vatican Museums also house a vast collection of sculptures, an Etruscan exhibit, an Egyptian exhibit, and more. There is a single entrance fee for both the Vatican Museums and the Sistine Chapel. Note that the complex is closed every Sunday, except for the last Sunday of the month, when it is open with free entry. However, on this day, the opening hours are shortened."
        }
      ]
    },
